snippet.textDisplay:
It's never wise to rush into any kind of judgement.


Don't kid yourself that UEFA are impartial or apolitical. UEFA courts sponsors like Gazprom and they held the Europa League final in Baku!! Their former president Platini was given a 4 year ban from football for being corrupt.....which was upheld by CAS!!


UEFA built their entire case on hacked emails which would be inadmissible in a normal court of law (but not in a kangaroo court) and apparently they didn't even consider the 100 page rebuttal sent by Man City. Wait until ALL the evidence comes out of CAS and the Swiss courts before drawing your own conclusions.


Just saying. I like to hear informed opinions but likening Man City to OJ Simpson is click bait.


Sheikh Mansoor's investment group bought Man CIty before UEFA changed the rules to protect the G14 cartel. UEFA have a monopoly on European club football. David Gill (Chief Executive of Man United for a decade) is the UEFA treasurer and a prominent member on the UEFA Executive Committee.


If City have done the crime then they'll do the time. Innocent until proven guilty. Both sides of the argument need to be heard.

snippet.textDisplay: So the big teams will remain big and the small will remain small...that’s what FFP is about. UEFA want the big, recognisable teams to be in the champions league, year in year out. If let’s say, Plymouth, got a new billionaire owner, they won’t ever be able to catch up to big teams so what’s the point of having a rich owner? They can’t spend more than what the team makes, (or brand value at this point). So are we retrospectively going to take away Blackburn’s title? Don’t see much difference between city and Blackburn’s title. Blackburn rovers bought Shearer who was the best striker around at the time, taking him from Man Utd. Was Blackburn as big as Man Utd? No, of course not, they needed investment to compete.

snippet.textDisplay:
As a Manchester United fan, I see both sides. It’s obvious City have took the piss with spending and rule bending and that, but blame FFP. How can you expect clubs with desire to take it to the next level without spending in this day and age? The rules need to be changed to allow smaller clubs to escape the trap of mediocrity in case a big owner with money and ambition does come in.

Having said that, I’ll never understand the resent and entitlement city as a club hold against UEFA which they’ve shown for years, as if they’ve got some sort of right to be a European elite. I think that’s why they’ve struggled in the UCL so much.
